JOHANNESBURG - Higher education minister Blade Nzimande and financial aid scheme chair Sizwe Nxasana will appear before the fees commission.The inquiry was set up by the president to investigate the feasibility of free higher education.The minister has previously stated that free higher education for all is not possible, urging those who can afford to pay to do so.Nzimande has also reiterated the state's commitment to supporting poor students via financial aid.Earlier this week, the ANC Youth League made its submissions.It's calling for the state ownership of public universities.eNCA